The place is good but the paella was not to the liking of my American palate.  The prawns sautéed in garlic were excellent.  Service was good.  Ambiance is excellent.  It's a bit pricey.  The problem I have with the paella is its blackened in the oven and the fish and rice are flavorless.  You cannot taste any subtleties.  Since this place was recommended by the ny times specifically for paella,  I was disappointed.
